            {
                "box": {
                    "id": "obj-9",
                    "linecount": 15,
                    "maxclass": "comment",
                    "numinlets": 1,
                    "numoutlets": 0,
                    "patching_rect": [ 865.0, 26.0, 439.0, 208.0 ],
                    "text": "Load a pre-analyzed corpus into all the required components.\n\nDatasets for nearest neighbor matching, fits for scaling nad regression, a coll for pulling up metadata, and a polybuffer to hold the samples themselves.\n\n@roundrobin = enables round robin sample matching so when a match is found twice in a row, a randomized selection is made within the nearest matches\n@invertmatching = returns matches that are *furthest* away\n@matchcount = sets the number of matches that are returned as iterated items, which will be played back as a \"chord\"\n@predictedweight = relative scaling of predicted descriptors when using predicted time scale (0. to 1.)\n@active = enables or disables the matching\n\nAlso takes onset detection attributes when refering a buffer directly."
                }
            },
